<SPAN class="specialtext">Torta</SPAN><p/>
Torta shows you where your disk space is going. It uses the graphical format used by the the awesome program <a href="http://www.methylblue.com/filelight/">filelight</a> to represent disk usage. Unlike <a href="http://www.methylblue.com/filelight/">filelight</a>, Torta does not need a graphical environment. Instead, Torta generates a flash file that can then be seen using any browser that has the <a href="http://www.macromedia.com/shockwave/download/download.cgi?P1_Prod_Version=ShockwaveFlash">flash plugin</a> installed.<p/>
Torta uses Gordon, a library that provides flash generation functionality.
<p/>
<SPAN class="specialtext">Examples</SPAN><p/>
